### Test Refresh Token Implementation

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login with the user
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Use the refresh token to get new access token
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 4. Get user profile with access token
GET http://localhost:3000/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Logout using refresh token (this will invalidate the refresh token)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 6. Try to use the refresh token after logout (should fail)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 7. Test logout when access token is expired (should work with refresh token)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "expired_refresh_token_here"
}

### 8. Test with expired refresh token (should return 401)
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "invalid_or_expired_token_here"
}
